         <abstract>
            <p>These two related communications from France written, respectively, in mid-September and in the closing days of November, 1967, provide an interesting summary of the economic and financial events themselves. They also offer an insight into the perspective of their unfolding as reflected in the mind of a professionally trained talented banker, and how it affected his investment decision making. Mr. Rist's letters give us some welcome information on what happened in France during the period under review. More importantly, they offer an empirical demonstration of the influence of these happenings on the sequence of thinking of a financial analyst.</p>
          </abstract>
